verbose_text: Thus, after carboxylation of HP [1- 13 C] pyruvate, 13 C must be released at the levels of PEPCK, isocitrate dehydrogenase and alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase, but the absence of a HP [13 C] bicarbonate signal suggests magnetization loss owing to T 1 relaxation in the multiple enzyme catalyzed reactions.
